from pathlib import Path

# Create README for templates folder with glossary and bibliography
templates_readme = """# Templates - Quick Reference

> **Purpose**: Hardware project management templates with industry-standard terminology and references

---

## Available Templates

| Template | Purpose | When to Use |
|----------|---------|-------------|
| [project-charter-hardware.md](./project-charter-hardware.md) | Define project scope, objectives, and constraints | Project kickoff |
| [risk-register-hardware.md](./risk-register-hardware.md) | Track and mitigate hardware-specific risks | Throughout project lifecycle |
| [phase-gate-checklist.md](./phase-gate-checklist.md) | Exit criteria for each development phase | Gate reviews (Concept → EVT → DVT → PVT → Production) |
| [sprint-planning-hardware.md](./sprint-planning-hardware.md) | Plan hardware sprints with lead-time tracking | Sprint planning (every 4-8 weeks) |
| [lessons-learned-template.md](./lessons-learned-template.md) | Capture insights for continuous improvement | Project completion or major milestones |

---

## Glossary of Terms & Acronyms

### Development Phases

| Term | Full Name | Description |
|------|-----------|-------------|
| **POC** | Proof of Concept | Initial feasibility demonstration |
| **EVT** | Engineering Validation Test | First functional prototypes (100-1K units) |
| **DVT** | Design Validation Test | Production-intent design validation (300-2K units) |
| **PVT** | Production Validation Test | Manufacturing process validation (1K-20K units) |
| **MP** | Mass Production | Volume production and shipment to customers |

### Project Management

| Term | Full Name | Description |
|------|-----------|-------------|
| **PM** | Project Manager | Person responsible for project coordination |
| **BOM** | Bill of Materials | List of components with part numbers and costs |
| **ECO** | Engineering Change Order | Formal process to modify design after freeze |
| **PRD** | Product Requirements Document | Detailed product specifications and requirements |
| **NRE** | Non-Recurring Engineering | One-time costs (tooling, prototypes, certification) |
| **MTBF** | Mean Time Between Failures | Reliability metric for product longevity |
| **DPMO** | Defects Per Million Opportunities | Quality metric for manufacturing |
| **NPS** | Net Promoter Score | Customer satisfaction metric (-100 to +100) |

### Manufacturing & Quality

| Term | Full Name | Description |
|------|-----------|-------------|
| **CM** | Contract Manufacturer | Third-party manufacturing partner |
| **DFM** | Design for Manufacturing | Design practices to improve manufacturability |
| **DFMA** | Design for Manufacturing and Assembly | Combined design optimization approach |
| **DFT** | Design for Test | Design practices to enable effective testing |
| **IQC** | Incoming Quality Control | Inspection of received components |
| **IPQC** | In-Process Quality Control | Quality checks during assembly |
| **FQC** | Final Quality Control | Final inspection before shipment |
| **FAI** | First Article Inspection | Verification of first production parts |
| **SPC** | Statistical Process Control | Statistical methods for process monitoring |
| **Cpk** | Process Capability Index | Measure of process variation (target >1.33) |
| **RMA** | Return Merchandise Authorization | Process for handling customer returns |

### Supply Chain

| Term | Full Name | Description |
|------|-----------|-------------|
| **EOL** | End of Life | Component discontinued by manufacturer |
| **MOQ** | Minimum Order Quantity | Smallest quantity supplier will sell |
| **LT** | Lead Time | Time from order to delivery |
| **JIT** | Just in Time | Inventory strategy minimizing stock |
| **PO** | Purchase Order | Formal order document to supplier |

### Testing & Compliance

| Term | Full Name | Description |
|------|-----------|-------------|
| **EMI** | Electromagnetic Interference | Unwanted electromagnetic emissions |
| **EMC** | Electromagnetic Compatibility | Ability to operate without causing/suffering EMI |
| **ESD** | Electrostatic Discharge | Static electricity that can damage electronics |
| **RoHS** | Restriction of Hazardous Substances | EU directive limiting toxic materials |
| **REACH** | Registration, Evaluation, Authorization of Chemicals | EU chemical regulation |
| **IP** | Ingress Protection | Rating for dust/water resistance (e.g., IP54) |
| **UL** | Underwriters Laboratories | Safety certification organization |
| **CE** | Conformité Européenne | European conformity marking |
| **FCC** | Federal Communications Commission | US regulatory agency for RF devices |
| **ITAR** | International Traffic in Arms Regulations | US export control for defense items |
| **EAR** | Export Administration Regulations | US export control for dual-use items |

### Technical

| Term | Full Name | Description |
|------|-----------|-------------|
| **PCB** | Printed Circuit Board | Board with electrical circuits |
| **MCU** | Microcontroller Unit | Integrated circuit with CPU, memory, I/O |
| **IC** | Integrated Circuit | Electronic circuit on semiconductor chip |
| **RTOS** | Real-Time Operating System | OS with guaranteed response times |
| **OTA** | Over-The-Air | Remote firmware update capability |
| **CFD** | Computational Fluid Dynamics | Thermal/airflow simulation |
| **DRC** | Design Rule Check | Automated verification of PCB design |
| **FMEA** | Failure Mode and Effect Analysis | Systematic risk analysis method |
| **PID** | Proportional-Integral-Derivative | Control algorithm for closed-loop systems |

### Agile & Scrum

| Term | Full Name | Description |
|------|-----------|-------------|
| **DoD** | Definition of Done | Criteria for completing a user story |
| **MVP** | Minimum Viable Product | Product with minimum features for launch |
| **EFFA** | Early Field Failure Analysis | Analysis of first customer failures |

---

## Bibliography & References

### Industry Standards & Guidelines

1. **Stage-Gate Process for Hardware Development**
   - Cooper, R.G. (2008). "Perspective: The Stage-Gate® Idea-to-Launch Process"
   - Source: Product Development Institute
   - [Stage-Gate Process Guide](https://www.stage-gate.com/)

2. **EVT, DVT, PVT Best Practices**
